WorkItem.ClosedComment: We've decided to not try to fix this for v1. The impact here isn't serious.
WorkItem.Description:
When a type name is not known, it's returned as an error twice in the output.

program.ts:
  var variable: UnknownType = 4;

> tsc program.ts
> /program.ts(1,14): The name 'UnknownType' does not exist in the current scope
> /program.ts(1,14): The name 'UnknownType' does not exist in the current scope
WorkItem.Summary: Unknown type name warning issued twice.

Comments.Message: Thanks for reporting this issue. We're now tracking this bug and going to fix it in our future releases!
